bug.summary: Failing to load the blank Ukrainian model
bug.description:
Hi, when trying to initialize the Ukrainian blank model, the following error is raised. spacy-nightly is installed via pip install spacy-nightly, while I know how to fix this, I'm wondering is this a packaging issue? <denchmark-code>import spacy >>> spacy.blank('uk')
Traceback (most recent call last): File "<pyshell#1>", line 1, in <module> spacy.blank('uk') File "D:\Python\lib\site-packages\spacy\__init__.py", line 26, in blank LangClass = util.get_lang_class(name) File "D:\Python\lib\site-packages\spacy\util.py", line 55, in get_lang_class module = importlib.import_module(".lang.%s" % lang, "spacy") File "D:\Python\lib\importlib\__init__.py", line 127, in import_module return _bootstrap._gcd_import(name[level:], package, level) File "<frozen importlib._bootstrap>", line 1006, in _gcd_import File "<frozen importlib._bootstrap>", line 983, in _find_and_load File "<frozen importlib._bootstrap>", line 967, in _find_and_load_unlocked File "<frozen importlib._bootstrap>", line 677, in _load_unlocked File "<frozen importlib._bootstrap_external>", line 728, in exec_module File "<frozen importlib._bootstrap>", line 219, in _call_with_frames_removed File "D:\Python\lib\site-packages\spacy\lang\uk\__init__.py", line 13, in <module> from .lemmatizer import UkrainianLemmatizer File "D:\Python\lib\site-packages\spacy\lang\uk\lemmatizer.py", line 18 "The Ukrainian lemmatizer requires the pymorphy2 library and ^ SyntaxError: EOL while scanning string literal </denchmark-code>
Operating System: Windows 10 64-bit Python Version Used: 3.7.2 64-bit spaCy Version Used: 2.1.0a9

comments.comment: Ugh, looks like this was a merge error that happened when syncing master with develop ðŸ˜ž (And it's not caught by our default CI, because we can't easily test the languages with external dependencies, at least not on each build.) Fixing!
